          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-2264 test: Create cpu load for testing",
        "message": "LU-2264 test: Create cpu load for testing\n\nIt can be useful to add extra cpu pressure for testing.\nClient nodes are likely to use extra resources.\n\nVia processor.sh we can add cpu load. It has a dumb bash loop\nthat is spaws by defaut 2 threads per cpu. It is adjustable\nas to the number of threads per cpu via the -m option.\n\nThis is nothing fancy just a way to introduce non IO cpu load.\n\nPerhaps we could add a -j to do a cpu power state change mode\nto interduce jitter to the system.\n\nSigned-off-by: Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I18a162f52eadc412110fe61d02c1ceaec7f99297\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
